						<summary>

						<p>On another pillar in the <hi rend="italic">mukhamaṇḍapa</hi> of the Venkaṭēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>1240 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1162 corresponding to 1240 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. Seems to register a gift of land measuring <hi rend="italic">kha</hi> at Aripalli, na. 10 under the irrigation of Jāyanacheṟuvu etc., by Aḍapa Mahādēvana-Peggada, the son of Muchchirāja, for offerings to the god Ishṭakāmīsvara Mahādēva.</p>						

						</summary>
